{
  "text": "[5] For full discussions of the STOWA Alvin and wax core data sets, see [CITATION_1] and Bergmanis et al. [1999] . [CITATION_2] discuss magnetic properties of basalt samples from this cruise. Earlier submersible observations within the survey areas are discussed by Renard et al. [1985] , [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] for discussions of the reflection seismics studies in this area. (Figure 1 ) is among the broadest along the southern EPR [CITATION_5] , with relatively smooth topography and a shallow seismic reflector at $1000 m depth, interpreted as the top of an axial magma reservoir . Local spreading rates are Figure 2 ). Note the higher magnetization associated with two pillow mounds at the bottom of the valley, low magnetization associated with the trough, and at a hydrothermal vent site.",
